{0 day11-container}

OCI container runtime primitives. {!Day11_container.Overlay} wraps Linux overlayfs
mount/umount via sudo, assembling read-only lowers and a writable
upper into a single merged rootfs. {!Day11_container.Runc} drives the [runc] OCI
runtime to execute containers, with stdout/stderr capture and
container lifecycle management. {!Day11_container.Oci_spec} generates [config.json]
templates with sensible defaults (namespaces, capabilities, seccomp
sync-masking, standard system mounts) parameterized by the rootfs
path. {!Day11_container.Mount} describes bind-mount specifications for the OCI spec.

Depends on {!page-exec} for subprocess execution. Has no knowledge of
opam, layers, or build orchestration — callers compose these
primitives with the layer and runner libraries.

